UN secretary-general Antonio Guterres is calling for African leaders to extend diplomacy to Sudan after the ousting of its former president and dictator, Omar al-Bashir, in 2019. According to the BBC, Guterres implored state leaders at the AU summit in Addis Ababa to include Sudan in domestic affairs. The secretary-general a said the UN would garner international support to ease Sudanâ€™s political transition. Plans to create an Africa-led peace effort to end the civil unrest in Libya and ways to mitigate increasing militant occupation throughout Africa were also discussed at the summit.